subject: Migration Update
msgSnippet: Greeting to all Quikscript members: To those who have donated money to fund the migration of Read_Alphabet to groups.io, let me express my sincere appreciation
messageBody:
Greeting to all Quikscript members:

To those who have donated money to fund the migration of Read_Alphabet
to groups.io, let me express my sincere appreciation for your
willingness to step up.  Before I set up the money pool with PayPal,
three of us had talked about paying for this premium account with groups.io.

We have met the goal I set with PayPal with a number of contributors. 
However, at this point, the goal has been met due to much larger amounts
being contributed by these 3 people.  If there are some of you who have
not yet contributed to the pool but had planned to, please go ahead and
makes those donations now. The pool will still accept additional monies.

If additional money comes in, that will enable the people who have put
much more into the pot to receive some of their donation back so that
the expense is shared more equally by the members of the group.  No
money over the $220 for the premium account will be kept.  Anything over
that amount will ultimately be returned to donating members in an
attempt to spread the cost as evenly as possible.

We had over 500 members with Yahoo Groups.  All of those e-mail
addresses should be transferred to the new group as the migrations
proceeds, but you can certainly go ahead and sign up now with groups.io
if you want to get a jump on the process.

Thanks again for your interest in Quikscript and in spreading it to
English speakers around the world.  I would love to see the number of
members grow significantly in 2020.  I know there are untold numbers of
people who have not heard about Quikscript who would welcome the
opportunity to write English in a script designed for the task and not
just grafted on to it like the Roman alphabet was.

Thank you for your participation.

Sincerely,

Paige Gabhart
